1
00:00:12,590 --> 00:00:13,400
Honey,

2
00:00:14,030 --> 00:00:15,910
this watch and our daughter

3
00:00:15,910 --> 00:00:17,480
are both gifts from me.

4
00:00:18,670 --> 00:00:20,670
I hope every time you check the time,

5
00:00:21,090 --> 00:00:22,710
you'll think of us.

6
00:00:23,390 --> 00:00:24,990
I know being a police officer

7
00:00:25,870 --> 00:00:26,660
means you have to work hard

8
00:00:26,660 --> 00:00:27,710
and take risks.

9
00:00:29,550 --> 00:00:30,950
I understand all of that.

10
00:00:31,640 --> 00:00:32,960
But I also hope

11
00:00:32,990 --> 00:00:35,190
that you can take good care of yourself,

12
00:00:35,540 --> 00:00:35,640
[No Access]

13
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:37,840
so you can take care of her in the future.

14
00:00:38,070 --> 00:00:39,670
Because you're a father now.

15
00:00:40,940 --> 00:00:41,900
How's it?

16
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:43,440
Do you like it?

17
00:03:09,340 --> 00:03:15,430
[The Perfect Suspect]

18
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:18,420
[Episode 7]

19
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:21,940
Does Xiao Dade usually get takeout here?

20
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:22,710
Not really.

21
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,280
He usually eats in.

22
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,120
Because for takeout,

23
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,280
we charge an extra yuan.

24
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,680
He's too stingy for that.

25
00:03:28,910 --> 00:03:30,150
Except that night...

26
00:03:30,470 --> 00:03:31,470
Here's your food.

27
00:03:31,910 --> 00:03:32,470
Thank you.

28
00:03:32,470 --> 00:03:34,530
Hello, one stir-fried pork, please.

29
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:35,560
Sure, grab a seat.

30
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:36,680
To-go.

31
00:03:36,740 --> 00:03:37,560
Okay.

32
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,840
That night he suddenly
wanted a takeout in a hurry.

33
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,970
Why was he in a hurry?

34
00:03:43,950 --> 00:03:45,300
I don't know about that.

35
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:47,360
I was busy with customers at the time.

36
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:49,760
Was there anything else unusual about him?

37
00:03:51,570 --> 00:03:52,460
Actually, yeah.

38
00:03:52,460 --> 00:03:54,190
He was acting strange all day.

39
00:03:58,190 --> 00:03:59,079
What did...

40
00:04:00,150 --> 00:04:01,410
that person look like?

41
00:04:04,470 --> 00:04:05,960
I didn't get a clear look.

42
00:04:07,300 --> 00:04:07,970
If there's nothing else,

43
00:04:07,970 --> 00:04:08,080
[Sheng's Hunan Diner]

44
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,240
I'll get back to work.

45
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:09,840
Alright.

46
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:10,440
Thank you.

47
00:04:11,190 --> 00:04:12,450
Sorry for the trouble.

48
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:14,960
Look, look.

49
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:16,870
The big scoop Xiao Dade mentioned

50
00:04:16,870 --> 00:04:17,720
must be this.

51
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:21,310
This one is indeed unbelievable

52
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:23,360
and shocking.

53
00:04:23,390 --> 00:04:23,450
I can't say too much about this right now.

54
00:04:23,450 --> 00:04:26,430
[Dade]

55
00:04:26,430 --> 00:04:28,870
I can only give you a little hint.

56
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:29,830
It points to

57
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:32,580
the head of a major

58
00:04:33,070 --> 00:04:36,060
pharmaceutical company in Xinggang.

59
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:36,390
[Dade]

60
00:04:36,390 --> 00:04:40,390
That gorgeous, brainy princess.

61
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:42,720
I saw it.

62
00:04:42,740 --> 00:04:45,420
What a rough patch
the princess's had lately.

63
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:46,990
But this is your guess,

64
00:04:47,010 --> 00:04:48,000
not my words.

65
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,550
I won't say it until the right time.

66
00:04:50,830 --> 00:04:52,960
Please don't make wild guesses, okay?

67
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,070
Are you meeting me

68
00:04:56,950 --> 00:04:58,750
as Lawyer Zhong

69
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,800
or Advisor Zhong?

70
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,190
Aren't they both me?

71
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:05,390
It's not the same.

72
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:07,510
There are things

73
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,560
I'll only say to Lawyer Zhong.

74
00:05:15,430 --> 00:05:17,360
Recently, there's someone called

75
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:19,850
Xiao Dade, an internet celebrity,

76
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:23,430
who insinuated about
Lyuyun Pharmaceuticals
during a livestream.

77
00:05:23,430 --> 00:05:24,870
Do you know about this?

78
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:26,120
Yes.

79
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,300
Our legal team is preparing the documents.

80
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:31,240
He needs to stop talking nonsense.

81
00:05:31,270 --> 00:05:32,870
He won't be talking anymore.

82
00:05:34,159 --> 00:05:35,040
He's dead.

83
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:37,450
What?

84
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,810
You seem surprised.

85
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,950
Are you suggesting

86
00:05:45,159 --> 00:05:46,890
that I shouldn't be surprised?

87
00:05:49,159 --> 00:05:50,550
To be honest,

88
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,310
it's been a sensitive period lately.

89
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,510
I'd rather avoid trouble,

90
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:58,590
but trouble keeps coming.

91
00:05:59,270 --> 00:06:01,680
Dirt keeps being thrown at me and Lyuyun.

92
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:03,940
Don't you find it strange?

93
00:06:11,190 --> 00:06:11,870
Ms. Zhao,

94
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,680
do you know

95
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,240
a little girl named Liao Yifan?

96
00:06:17,310 --> 00:06:18,120
Who?

97
00:06:18,390 --> 00:06:19,390
Five years ago,

98
00:06:20,870 --> 00:06:23,000
she was hit by a car and died

99
00:06:23,630 --> 00:06:25,160
in a hit-and-run accident.

100
00:06:26,390 --> 00:06:29,050
I don't want to answer
these strange questions.

101
00:06:31,950 --> 00:06:33,170
[Advisor ID]

102
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,180
You have to answer.

103
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,810
Hello, Director Zhang.

104
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,550
I'm Zhao Qian.

105
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,040
I'd like to ask,

106
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,840
can your special advisor

107
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:02,630
conduct interviews without

108
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,240
police present?

109
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:08,840
Yes,

110
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:11,660
he's sitting right in front of me now.

111
00:07:30,790 --> 00:07:33,500
[Incoming call: Master]

112
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:36,760
Advisor Zhong,

113
00:07:37,510 --> 00:07:39,040
next time you want to see me,

114
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:42,720
remember to make
an appointment with my assistant.

115
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,010
You seem quite familiar

116
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:48,540
with our investigation procedures.

117
00:07:50,950 --> 00:07:51,800
Apologies.

118
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,950
We'll meet again.

119
00:08:08,540 --> 00:08:09,270
Master,

120
00:08:09,950 --> 00:08:11,390
how did you get here so quickly?

121
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:13,520
Why did you come to see Zhao Qian alone?

122
00:08:16,290 --> 00:08:18,770
Can't I catch up with my dance partner?

123
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:20,480
Don't play word games with me.

124
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,870
Just because you have the Advisor ID

125
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:23,750
doesn't mean you can run around
causing trouble for the team.

126
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:24,480
Zhong Ning, let me ask you,

127
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,040
do you know conducting
investigations alone is illegal?

128
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,120
Are you even a cop?

129
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:30,580
You took off
that uniform yourself long ago!

130
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,000
President Cao even

131
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,320
called the mayor—

132
00:08:33,340 --> 00:08:35,320
asking if a task force
advisor was sent to him.

133
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,480
I took the heat for you!

134
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:38,280
You think I'm willing to do that?

135
00:08:42,020 --> 00:08:42,669
Let me tell you,

136
00:08:42,669 --> 00:08:44,270
I just can't stand
your disregard for rules

137
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:45,670
and your arrogant attitude.

138
00:08:45,670 --> 00:08:48,600
When have you not
caused harm to others and yourself?

139
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,150
When?

140
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,270
Say it if you have the guts!

141
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:53,390
Seven years ago!

142
00:08:54,870 --> 00:08:57,130
Did I make myself clear? Seven years ago!

143
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:05,880
I just don't understand

144
00:09:07,270 --> 00:09:08,870
why Master brought you back.

145
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:10,000
Then tell Master

146
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:10,750
to fire me right now.

147
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:12,030
I'll fire you right now!

148
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:13,870
You think I want to work with you?

149
00:09:13,870 --> 00:09:15,670
You think I want to face you?

150
00:09:17,310 --> 00:09:18,440
Well, I'm willing to face you.

151
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:19,210
Zhong Ning!

152
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:21,420
-Calm down.
-I'm willing to face you!

153
00:09:21,790 --> 00:09:22,290
Captain,

154
00:09:22,290 --> 00:09:24,150
calm down. I'll talk to him later.

155
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:27,050
What's it got to do with you?

156
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:30,920
How long are you going to keep fighting?

157
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:32,960
Another seven years?

158
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:40,600
Get in the car.

159
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:44,550
You get in too.

160
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:51,370
I said get in the car!

161
00:10:29,290 --> 00:10:30,820
Master, where are we going?

162
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,860
You'll know when we get there.

163
00:10:42,740 --> 00:10:49,420
[Blissful Nightclub]

164
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:56,600
This nightclub has been gone for years.

165
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:03,080
But I'm afraid
it still exists in your hearts.

166
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,150
You've been running from it,

167
00:11:05,150 --> 00:11:06,480
too scared to come back.

168
00:11:06,670 --> 00:11:08,440
I bet neither of you

169
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,440
have stepped on this street

170
00:11:11,870 --> 00:11:14,510
in the past seven years.

171
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,460
Can you avoid it for a lifetime?

172
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:21,200
Are you going to
live your whole life like this?

173
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,200
Say something!

174
00:11:26,290 --> 00:11:30,110
[Blissful Nightclub]

175
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:34,610
[Seven years ago]

176
00:11:37,270 --> 00:11:39,600
I have to work overtime
tonight to make slides.

177
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,790
There's soup in the fridge.

178
00:11:40,790 --> 00:11:42,050
Remember to heat it up.

179
00:11:49,010 --> 00:11:50,570
[I have to work overtime tonight to make slides.
There's soup in the fridge. Remember to heat it up.]

180
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,720
Sir, please wipe your hands.

181
00:12:08,050 --> 00:12:09,690
You're quite pretty.

182
00:12:11,150 --> 00:12:11,790
Take it.

183
00:12:12,330 --> 00:12:13,890
Here's your tip.

184
00:12:17,790 --> 00:12:18,860
So smooth.

185
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:26,610
Quite a character.

186
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:32,410
How's it going?

187
00:12:32,870 --> 00:12:34,250
There's a problem
with the detention warrant.

188
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:35,600
They'll send it over once it's ready.

189
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:37,390
We'll have to wait
another five minutes, I guess.

190
00:12:37,390 --> 00:12:39,160
By the time it's ready, they'll be gone.

191
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:40,190
Dajun, move!

192
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:42,750
Move.

193
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:46,680
What are we playing?

194
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:47,480
Four twos!

195
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:47,960
Call.

196
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,270
-Drink.
-You and him.

197
00:12:49,270 --> 00:12:49,900
Boss!

198
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:51,040
Boss!

199
00:12:51,150 --> 00:12:51,900
Police!

200
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:52,840
Police!

201
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:53,840
-Let's go.
-Police!

202
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:54,390
Hurry.

203
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:55,370
Hurry.

204
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:55,840
Police.

205
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:56,630
Go, go, go!

206
00:12:56,750 --> 00:12:57,960
Keep up! Hurry!

207
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:58,750
Make way!

208
00:13:00,290 --> 00:13:01,030
Stop!

209
00:13:01,470 --> 00:13:02,170
Don't move!

210
00:13:02,190 --> 00:13:03,260
-This way.
-Police!

211
00:13:03,260 --> 00:13:03,870
Freeze!

212
00:13:03,870 --> 00:13:04,910
-Stop!
-This way!

213
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:05,910
Against the wall!

214
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,000
Against the wall!

215
00:13:07,030 --> 00:13:07,870
Stay still!

216
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:08,550
Don't move!

217
00:13:08,670 --> 00:13:09,400
Stop!

218
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,570
-Stop! Stop!
-This way.

219
00:13:13,140 --> 00:13:13,800
Don't move!

220
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:15,120
Easy, easy!

221
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:16,170
-Don't move.
-Easy, easy.

222
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:16,720
Behave yourself!

223
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:17,430
Stop!

224
00:13:27,390 --> 00:13:27,870
What are you doing?

225
00:13:27,870 --> 00:13:28,530
Don't move!

226
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:07,300
Gang,

227
00:14:08,190 --> 00:14:09,130
don't go there.

228
00:14:10,740 --> 00:14:11,940
Don't go there, Gang.

229
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:19,790
[In Loving Memory of Wife Zheng Wenjing]

230
00:15:38,050 --> 00:15:39,900
♪ Snow turns to ice, then melts to water ♪

231
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:40,770
Master.

232
00:15:44,370 --> 00:15:45,170
Wenjing once told me

233
00:15:45,170 --> 00:15:48,120
♪ Water rises as vapor,
then falls as rain ♪

234
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:50,510
she loved seeing me in uniform.

235
00:15:52,330 --> 00:15:53,730
♪ Raindrops into the sea,
from the sea swims a fish ♪

236
00:15:53,730 --> 00:15:55,190
She thought I looked cool.

237
00:15:59,550 --> 00:16:01,540
♪ Swimming upstream for thousands of miles,
just to return home ♪

238
00:16:01,540 --> 00:16:05,070
[In Loving Memory of Wife Zheng Wenjing]

239
00:16:05,390 --> 00:16:06,300
I want her

240
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:09,910
♪ Waiting for you, across the vast land ♪

241
00:16:09,910 --> 00:16:12,240
to see me in my uniform one last time.

242
00:16:13,690 --> 00:16:13,840
♪ Running to you,
with tears but no words ♪

243
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,770
She won't be able to see it anymore.

244
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:18,570
What are you going to do?

245
00:16:20,830 --> 00:16:27,940
♪ Holding you, never part again ♪

246
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:28,760
Starting tomorrow,

247
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:34,200
♪ Loving you, so my soul can rest ♪

248
00:16:34,610 --> 00:16:36,150
I'm no longer a cop.

249
00:16:39,510 --> 00:16:40,480
What do you mean?

250
00:16:50,030 --> 00:16:50,910
Master,

251
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:57,120
Renxi needs someone to take care of her.

252
00:16:59,380 --> 00:17:00,450
Her illness

253
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:03,560
will cost a lot of money.

254
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:07,000
♪ Snow turns to ice, then melts to water ♪

255
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,260
This is also Wenjing's

256
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:10,760
unfinished concern.

257
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:16,720
♪ Water rises as vapor,
then falls as rain ♪

258
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:17,910
For the rest of my life,

259
00:17:17,910 --> 00:17:19,349
♪ Raindrops into the sea,
from the sea swims a fish ♪

260
00:17:19,349 --> 00:17:20,810
I have only one thing to do:

261
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:23,750
to take good care of Renxi,

262
00:17:25,020 --> 00:17:26,109
♪ Swimming upstream for thousands of miles,
just to return home ♪

263
00:17:26,109 --> 00:17:27,200
cure her illness,

264
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,880
and help her grow up

265
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:31,950
healthy.

266
00:17:31,950 --> 00:17:38,520
♪ Waiting for you, across the vast land ♪

267
00:17:39,220 --> 00:17:40,750
♪ Running to you,
with tears but no words ♪

268
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:42,350
You want to punish yourself?

269
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:44,070
Well, I deserve it.

270
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:45,680
Five minutes.

271
00:17:46,180 --> 00:17:48,440
♪ Holding you, never part again ♪

272
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:49,830
Just five more minutes.

273
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:50,960
Shut up!

274
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:57,030
♪ Loving you, so my soul can rest ♪

275
00:17:57,030 --> 00:17:59,290
I've always taken you as my own children.

276
00:17:59,950 --> 00:18:01,270
You two are brothers.

277
00:18:26,770 --> 00:18:28,310
I really want to slap you.

278
00:18:30,930 --> 00:18:31,890
I'm sorry.

279
00:19:40,110 --> 00:19:41,370
It's been seven years.

280
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:44,310
You still haven't
moved on from this street.

281
00:19:45,270 --> 00:19:46,590
It's never-ending.

282
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:49,000
When will it end on earth?

283
00:19:51,270 --> 00:19:53,530
If Wenjing's spirit is watching over us,

284
